  53class DBInfo:
  54  def __init__(self, namedb):
  55        '''
  56        For a specific database (call namedb), returns information on the epidemiological variables.
  57        Those informations are used later on in covid19.py.
  58        It returns a dictionnary with:
  59            * key: epidemiological variable
  60            * values:
  61                - new variable name for pycoa purpose, if needed. By default is an empty string ''
  62                - desciption of the variable. By default is an empty string '' but it is highly recommended to describe the variable
  63                - url of the csv where the epidemiological variable is
  64                - url of the master i.e where some general description could be located. By default is an empty string ''
  65        '''
  66        self.dbparsed = pd.DataFrame()
  67        mydico = {}
  68        self.separator = {}
  69        self.db = namedb
  70        self.db_world = False
  71        alldb  = list(_db_list_dict.keys())
  72        if self.db not in alldb:
  73            raise CoaDbError('Unknown ' + namedb + '. Available database so far in PyCoa are : ' + str(alldb), file=sys.stderr)
  74        else:
  75            try:
  76                if self.get_dblistdico(namedb)[1] == 'nation': # world wide dba
  77                    self.db_world = True
  78                    self.geo = coge.GeoManager('name')
  79                    self.geo_all = 'world'
  80                else: # local db
  81                    self.db_world = False
  82                    self.geo = coge.GeoCountry(self.get_dblistdico(namedb)[0])
  83                    if self.get_dblistdico(namedb)[1] == 'region':
  84                        self.geo_all = self.geo.get_region_list()
  85                    elif self.get_dblistdico(namedb)[1] == 'subregion':
  86                        self.geo_all = self.geo.get_subregion_list()
  87                    else:
  88                        CoaError('Granularity problem, neither region or subregion')
  89                # specific reading of data according to the db
  90                self.get_parsing(namedb)
  91            except:
  92                raise CoaDbError("An error occured while parsing data of "+self.get_db()+". This may be due to a data format modification. "
  93                    "You may contact support@pycoa.fr. Thanks.")
  94            # some info
  95            self.get_echoinfo()
  96
  97  def get_echoinfo(self):
  98      info('Few information concernant the selected database : ', self.get_db())
  99      info('Available key-words, which ∈', sorted(self.get_available_keywords()))
 100      info('Example of where : ',  ', '.join(random.choices(self.get_locations(), k=min(5,len(self.get_locations() ))   )), ' ...')
 101      info('Last date data ', self.get_dates().max())

 347                           raise ValueError
 348                       try:
 349                           date=datetime.date(y,m,d)

 353                               date=datetime.date(y,m,d)

 861    ''' For center for Systems Science and Engineering (CSSE) at Johns Hopkins University
 862        COVID-19 Data Repository by the see homepage: https://github.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19

 870    drop_field = kwargs.get('drop_field', None)

 874    mypd = pd.DataFrame()
 875    pandas_list = []

 880        if rename_columns:
 881            if db == 'rki':
 882                mypd = mypd.set_index('time_iso8601').T.reset_index().rename(columns=rename_columns)
 883            else:
 884                mypd = mypd.rename(columns=rename_columns)
 885        if drop_columns:
 886            mypd = mypd.drop(columns=drop_columns)
 887        mypd = mypd.melt(id_vars=['where'],var_name="date",value_name=self.get_url_original_keywords()[url][0])
 888        if drop_field:
 889          for key,val in drop_field.items():
 890              mypd =  mypd[~mypd[key].isin(val)]
 891        mypd=mypd.groupby(['where','date']).sum().reset_index()
 892        pandas_list.append(mypd)
 893    self.available_keywords = flat_list(self.available_keywords)
 894    uniqloc = list(pandas_list[0]['where'].unique())
 895    oldloc = uniqloc
 896    codedico={}
 897    toremove = None
 898    newloc = None
 899    location_is_code = False
 900    if self.db_world:
 901      d_loc_s = collections.OrderedDict(zip(uniqloc,self.geo.to_standard(uniqloc,output='list',db=self.get_db(),interpret_region=True)))
 902      self.slocation = list(d_loc_s.values())
 903      g=coge.GeoManager('iso3')
 904      codename = collections.OrderedDict(zip(self.slocation,g.to_standard(self.slocation,output='list',db=self.get_db(),interpret_region=True)))
 905    else:

 907          pdcodename = self.geo.get_subregion_list()
 908          self.slocation = uniqloc
 909          codename = collections.OrderedDict(zip(self.slocation,list(pdcodename.loc[pdcodename.code_subregion.isin(self.slocation)]['name_subregion'])))
 910          if db == 'jhu-usa':
 911              d_loc_s = collections.OrderedDict(zip(uniqloc,list(pdcodename.loc[pdcodename.name_subregion.isin(uniqloc)]['code_subregion'])))
 912              self.slocation = list(d_loc_s.keys())
 913              codename = d_loc_s
 914          if db == 'rki':
 915              d_loc_s = collections.OrderedDict(zip(uniqloc,list(pdcodename.loc[pdcodename.code_subregion.isin(uniqloc)]['name_subregion'])))
 916              self.slocation = list(d_loc_s.values())
 917              codename = d_loc_s
 918              location_is_code = True
 919              def notuse():
 920                  count_values=collections.Counter(d_loc_s.values())
 921                  duplicates_location = list({k:v for k,v in count_values.items() if v>1}.keys())
 922                  def findkeywithvalue(dico,what):
 923                      a=[]
 924                      for k,v in dico.items():
 925                          if v == what:
 926                              a.append(k)
 927                      return a
 928                  codedupli={i:findkeywithvalue(d_loc_s,i) for i in duplicates_location}
 929      elif self.get_dblistdico(db)[1] == 'region':
 930          codename = self.geo.get_data().set_index('name_region')['code_region'].to_dict()

 933          raise CoaTypeError('Not a region nors ubregion ... sorry but what is it ?')

 936

 939      result['where'] = result['where'].map(codename)

 942          result['where'] = result['where'].map(d_loc_s)
 943      result['codelocation'] = result['where'].map(codename)

 945    tmp = pd.DataFrame()
 946    if 'Kosovo' in uniqloc:
 947      #Kosovo is Serbia ! with geo.to_standard
 948      tmp=(result.loc[result['where'].isin(['Serbia'])]).groupby('date').sum(numeric_only=True).reset_index()
 949      tmp['where'] = 'Serbia'
 950      tmp['codelocation'] = 'SRB'
 951      kw = [i for i in self.available_keywords]
 952      colpos=['where', 'date'] + kw + ['codelocation']
 953      tmp = tmp[colpos]
 954      result = result.loc[~result['where'].isin(['Serbia'])]
 955      result = pd.concat([result,tmp])
 956
 957    result = result.copy()
 958    result.loc[:,'date'] = pd.to_datetime(result['date'],errors='coerce',utc=True).dt.date
 959    result = result.sort_values(by=['where','date'])
 960    result = result.reset_index(drop=True)
 961    if db == 'jhu-usa':
 962      col=result.columns.tolist()
 963      ncol=col[:2]+col[2:]
 964      result=result[ncol]
 965      self.available_keywords+=['Population']

 969  def row_where_csv_parser(self,**kwargs):
 970     '''
 971        Parse and convert the database cvs file to a pandas structure
 972     '''
 973     kwargs_test(kwargs,['url','cast','separator','encoding','constraints','rename_columns','keep_field','drop_field','quotechar'],
 974         'Bad args used in the csv2pandas() function.')
 975     url = kwargs.get('url', None)
 976     cast = kwargs.get('cast', None)
 977     separator = kwargs.get('separator', None)
 978     constraints = kwargs.get('constraints', None)
 979     rename_columns = kwargs.get('rename_columns', None)
 980     drop_field = kwargs.get('drop_field', None)
 981     keep_field = kwargs.get('keep_field', None)
 982     self.available_keywords = self.get_url_original_keywords()[url]
 983     #self.database_url.append(url)
 984     encoding = kwargs.get('encoding', None)
 985     if encoding:
 986         encoding = encoding
 987     quoting=0
 988     pandas_db = pd.read_csv(get_local_from_url(url,10000), sep=separator, encoding = encoding,
 989          keep_default_na=False,na_values='',header=0,quoting=quoting, dtype=cast,low_memory=False) # cached for 2 hours
 990     if constraints:
 991         for key,val in constraints.items():
 992             if key in pandas_db.columns:
 993                 pandas_db = pandas_db.loc[pandas_db[key] == val]
 994                 pandas_db = pandas_db.drop(columns=key)
 995     if rename_columns:
 996             pandas_db = pandas_db.rename(columns=rename_columns)
 997     if drop_field:
 998         for key,val in drop_field.items():
 999             pandas_db =  pandas_db[~pandas_db[key].isin(val)]
1000     if 'semaine' in  pandas_db.columns:
1001         pandas_db['semaine'] = [ week_to_date(i) for i in pandas_db['semaine']]
1002         pandas_db = pandas_db.rename(columns={'semaine':'date'})
1003     if keep_field:
1004         pandas_db =  pandas_db[keep_field]
1005
1006     if self.db == "govcy":
1007        pandas_db['date'] = pd.to_datetime(pandas_db['date'], errors='coerce', format="%d/%m/%Y").dt.date
1008     else:
1009        pandas_db['date'] = pd.to_datetime(pandas_db['date'], errors='coerce', infer_datetime_format=True).dt.date
1010
1011     #pandas_db['date'] = pd.to_datetime(pandas_db['date'],errors='coerce',infer_datetime_format=True).dt.date
1012     if self.get_dblistdico(self.db)[1] == 'nation' and self.get_dblistdico(self.db)[0] in ['FRA','CYP'] or \
1013         self.db=="spfnational":
1014         pandas_db['where'] = self.get_dblistdico(self.db)[2]
1015     pandas_db = pandas_db.sort_values(['where','date'])
1016     return pandas_db

1026          not_UN_nation_dict=['Kosovo','Serbia']

1028          tmp['where'] = 'Serbia'

1030          cols = tmp.columns.tolist()

1032          tmp = tmp[cols]
1033          mypandas = mypandas.loc[~mypandas['where'].isin(not_UN_nation_dict)]
1034          mypandas = pd.concat([tmp,mypandas])
1035      if 'iso_code' in mypandas.columns:
1036          mypandas['iso_code'] = mypandas['iso_code'].dropna().astype(str)
1037          mypandasori=mypandas.copy()
1038          strangeiso3tokick = [i for i in mypandasori['iso_code'].dropna().unique() if not len(i)==3 ]
1039          mypandasori = mypandas.loc[~mypandas.iso_code.isin(strangeiso3tokick)]
1040          mypandasori = mypandasori.drop(columns=['where'])
1041          mypandasori = mypandasori.rename(columns={'iso_code':'where'})
1042          if self.db == 'owid':
1043              onlyowid = mypandas.loc[mypandas.iso_code.isin(strangeiso3tokick)]
1044              onlyowid = onlyowid.copy()
1045              onlyowid.loc[:,'where'] = onlyowid['where'].apply(lambda x : 'owid_'+x)
1046          mypandas = mypandasori

1056          sub2reg = dict(gd.values)

1062          mypandas['where'] = mypandas['where'].apply(lambda x: x.title().replace('Do', 'do').replace('Da','da').replace('De','de'))
1063          uniqloc = list(mypandas['where'].unique())
1064          sub2reg = dict(gd.values)
1065          #sub2reg = collections.OrderedDict(zip(uniqloc,list(gd.loc[gd.name_subregion.isin(uniqloc)]['name_region'])))
1066          mypandas['where'] = mypandas['where'].map(sub2reg)
1067          mypandas = mypandas.loc[~mypandas['where'].isnull()]
1068       # filling subregions.
1069          gd = self.geo.get_data()[['code_region','name_region']]
1070          uniqloc = list(mypandas['where'].unique())
1071          name2code = collections.OrderedDict(zip(uniqloc,list(gd.loc[gd.name_region.isin(uniqloc)]['code_region'])))
1072          mypandas = mypandas.loc[~mypandas['where'].isnull()]
1073
1074      codename = None
1075      location_is_code = False
1076      uniqloc = list(mypandas['where'].unique()) # if possible location from csv are codelocationv
1077      if self.db_world:

1080          if self.db in ['govcy','europa']:

1103          mypandas = mypandas.reset_index(drop=True)
1104      mypandas = mypandas.groupby(['where','date']).sum(min_count=1).reset_index() # summing in case of multiple dates (e.g. in opencovid19 data). But keep nan if any

1106          location_is_code=False

1125  def get_mainpandas(self,**kwargs):
1126    '''
1127         * defaut :
1128              - location = None
1129              - date = None
1130              - selected_col = None
1131             Return the csv file to the mainpandas structure
1132             index | location              | date      | keywords1       |  keywords2    | ...| keywordsn
1133             -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1134             0     |        location1      |    1      |  l1-val1-1      |  l1-val2-1    | ...|  l1-valn-1
1135             1     |        location1      |    2      |  l1-val1-2      |  l1-val2-2    | ...|  l1-valn-2
1136             2     |        location1      |    3      |  l1-val1-3      |  l1-val2-3    | ...|  l1-valn-3
1137                              ...
1138             p     |       locationp       |    1      |   lp-val1-1     |  lp-val2-1    | ...| lp-valn-1
1139             ...
1140         * location : list of location (None : all location)
1141         * date : latest date to retrieve (None : max date)
1142         * selected_col: column to keep according to get_available_keywords (None : all get_available_keywords)
1143                         N.B. location column is added
1144     '''
1145    kwargs_test(kwargs,['where', 'date', 'selected_col'],
1146                 'Bad args used in the get_stats() function.')
1147
1148    where = kwargs.get('where', None)
1149    selected_col = kwargs.get('selected_col', None)
1150    watch_date = kwargs.get('date', None)
1151    if where:
1152         if not isinstance(where, list):
1153             clist = ([where]).copy()
1154         else:
1155             clist = (where).copy()
1156         if not all(isinstance(c, str) for c in clist):
1157             raise CoaWhereError("Location via the where keyword should be given as strings. ")
1158         if self.db_world:
1159             self.geo.set_standard('name')
1160             if self.db == 'owid':
1161                 owid_name = [c for c in clist if c.startswith('owid_')]
1162                 clist = [c for c in clist if not c.startswith('owid_')]
1163             clist=self.geo.to_standard(clist,output='list', interpret_region=True)
1164         else:
1165             clist=clist+self.geo.get_subregions_from_list_of_region_names(clist)
1166             if clist in ['FRA','USA','ITA'] :
1167                 clist=self.geo_all['code_subregion'].to_list()
1168
1169         clist=list(set(clist)) # to suppress duplicate countries
1170         diff_locations = list(set(clist) - set(self.get_locations()))
1171         clist = [i for i in clist if i not in diff_locations]
1172         filtered_pandas = self.mainpandas.copy()
1173         if len(clist) == 0 and len(owid_name) == 0:
1174             raise CoaWhereError('Not a correct location found according to the where option given.')
1175         if self.db == 'owid':
1176             clist+=owid_name
1177         filtered_pandas = filtered_pandas.loc[filtered_pandas['where'].isin(clist)]
1178         if watch_date:
1179             check_valid_date(watch_date)
1180             mydate = pd.to_datetime(watch_date).date()
1181         else :
1182             mydate = filtered_pandas.date.max()
1183         filtered_pandas = filtered_pandas.loc[filtered_pandas.date==mydate].reset_index(drop=True)
1184         if selected_col:
1185             l = selected_col
1186         else:
1187             l=list(self.get_available_keywords())
1188         l.insert(0, 'where')
1189         filtered_pandas = filtered_pandas[l]
1190         return filtered_pandas
1191    self.mainpandas = self.mainpandas.reset_index(drop=True)
1192    return self.mainpandas

  56        '''
  57        For a specific database (call namedb), returns information on the epidemiological variables.
  58        Those informations are used later on in covid19.py.
  59        It returns a dictionnary with:
  60            * key: epidemiological variable
  61            * values:
  62                - new variable name for pycoa purpose, if needed. By default is an empty string ''
  63                - desciption of the variable. By default is an empty string '' but it is highly recommended to describe the variable
  64                - url of the csv where the epidemiological variable is
  65                - url of the master i.e where some general description could be located. By default is an empty string ''
  66        '''
  67        self.dbparsed = pd.DataFrame()
  68        mydico = {}
  69        self.separator = {}
  70        self.db = namedb
  71        self.db_world = False
  72        alldb  = list(_db_list_dict.keys())
  73        if self.db not in alldb:
  74            raise CoaDbError('Unknown ' + namedb + '. Available database so far in PyCoa are : ' + str(alldb), file=sys.stderr)
  75        else:
  76            try:
  77                if self.get_dblistdico(namedb)[1] == 'nation': # world wide dba
  78                    self.db_world = True
  79                    self.geo = coge.GeoManager('name')
  80                    self.geo_all = 'world'
  81                else: # local db
  82                    self.db_world = False
  83                    self.geo = coge.GeoCountry(self.get_dblistdico(namedb)[0])
  84                    if self.get_dblistdico(namedb)[1] == 'region':
  85                        self.geo_all = self.geo.get_region_list()
  86                    elif self.get_dblistdico(namedb)[1] == 'subregion':
  87                        self.geo_all = self.geo.get_subregion_list()
  88                    else:
  89                        CoaError('Granularity problem, neither region or subregion')
  90                # specific reading of data according to the db
  91                self.get_parsing(namedb)
  92            except:
  93                raise CoaDbError("An error occured while parsing data of "+self.get_db()+". This may be due to a data format modification. "
  94                    "You may contact support@pycoa.fr. Thanks.")
  95            # some info
  96            self.get_echoinfo()
  97

 101      info('Example of where : ',  ', '.join(random.choices(self.get_locations(), k=min(5,len(self.get_locations() ))   )), ' ...')

1126  def get_mainpandas(self,**kwargs):
1127    '''
1128         * defaut :
1129              - location = None
1130              - date = None
1131              - selected_col = None
1132             Return the csv file to the mainpandas structure
1133             index | location              | date      | keywords1       |  keywords2    | ...| keywordsn
1134             -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1135             0     |        location1      |    1      |  l1-val1-1      |  l1-val2-1    | ...|  l1-valn-1
1136             1     |        location1      |    2      |  l1-val1-2      |  l1-val2-2    | ...|  l1-valn-2
1137             2     |        location1      |    3      |  l1-val1-3      |  l1-val2-3    | ...|  l1-valn-3
1138                              ...
1139             p     |       locationp       |    1      |   lp-val1-1     |  lp-val2-1    | ...| lp-valn-1
1140             ...
1141         * location : list of location (None : all location)
1142         * date : latest date to retrieve (None : max date)
1143         * selected_col: column to keep according to get_available_keywords (None : all get_available_keywords)
1144                         N.B. location column is added
1145     '''
1146    kwargs_test(kwargs,['where', 'date', 'selected_col'],
1147                 'Bad args used in the get_stats() function.')
1148
1149    where = kwargs.get('where', None)
1150    selected_col = kwargs.get('selected_col', None)
1151    watch_date = kwargs.get('date', None)
1152    if where:
1153         if not isinstance(where, list):
1154             clist = ([where]).copy()
1155         else:
1156             clist = (where).copy()
1157         if not all(isinstance(c, str) for c in clist):
1158             raise CoaWhereError("Location via the where keyword should be given as strings. ")
1159         if self.db_world:
1160             self.geo.set_standard('name')
1161             if self.db == 'owid':
1162                 owid_name = [c for c in clist if c.startswith('owid_')]
1163                 clist = [c for c in clist if not c.startswith('owid_')]
1164             clist=self.geo.to_standard(clist,output='list', interpret_region=True)
1165         else:
1166             clist=clist+self.geo.get_subregions_from_list_of_region_names(clist)
1167             if clist in ['FRA','USA','ITA'] :
1168                 clist=self.geo_all['code_subregion'].to_list()
1169
1170         clist=list(set(clist)) # to suppress duplicate countries
1171         diff_locations = list(set(clist) - set(self.get_locations()))
1172         clist = [i for i in clist if i not in diff_locations]
1173         filtered_pandas = self.mainpandas.copy()
1174         if len(clist) == 0 and len(owid_name) == 0:
1175             raise CoaWhereError('Not a correct location found according to the where option given.')
1176         if self.db == 'owid':
1177             clist+=owid_name
1178         filtered_pandas = filtered_pandas.loc[filtered_pandas['where'].isin(clist)]
1179         if watch_date:
1180             check_valid_date(watch_date)
1181             mydate = pd.to_datetime(watch_date).date()
1182         else :
1183             mydate = filtered_pandas.date.max()
1184         filtered_pandas = filtered_pandas.loc[filtered_pandas.date==mydate].reset_index(drop=True)
1185         if selected_col:
1186             l = selected_col

1188             l=list(self.get_available_keywords())

1190         filtered_pandas = filtered_pandas[l]
